other_tests.findings: The liver demonstrates diffusely increased echogenicity, most compatible with fatty infiltration. No focal liver lesions are identified. No intra- or extra-hepatic biliary dilatation with the common bile duct measuring up to 5 mm. Main portal vein is patent with appropriate hepatopetal flow. The gallbladder is mildly distended. No gallstones are identified. There is a trace amount of pericholecystic fluid. No definitive gallbladder wall thickening or edema is identified.
